         "qid": "19",
         "q": [
            "HOW DO I CREATE A VIRTUAL FIREWALL"
         ],
         "a": "Login to your cloud dashboard with userid / password provided in an email.\n\n(IMPORTANT: Dashboard uses features from HTML5, please use browser that fully supports HTML5. Some examples are Firefox, Google Chrome, Opera).\n–\ndashboard_login\n–\n\nIn dashboard, expand “Network” from left navigation menu.\n–\ndashboard_panel_network\n–\nSelect “Firewalls” section. (IMPORTANT: Once a firewall is successfully created, the default is to drop all traffic unless specified in “Firewall Rules”).\n–\nfirewalls_create_firewall\n–\nGo to “Firewall Rules” tab.\n–\nfirewalls_tab_rules\n–\nClick “+ Add Rule” button to create your first rule, or additional rules.\n–\nfirewalls_tab_rules_add_rule\n–\nName, recommended format is “flowtype-network-action-ports” (Example: ingress-dmz-allow-80, this name defines in-bound traffic to DMZ network that is allowed over port 80).\nDescription can be helpful to understand rules.\nProtocol\nAction\nSource IP Address/Subnet\nDestination IP Address/Subnet\nSource Port/Port Range\nDestination Port/Port Range\nClick “Add”\n–\nfirewalls_tab_rules_list\n–\nGo to “Firewall Policies” tab.\n–\nfirewalls_tab_policies\n–\nClick “+ Add Policy” button to create your firewall policy.\nName for the policy.\nDescription.\n–\nfirewalls_tab_policies_add_policy\n–\nClick on Rules tab to add / remove rules from policy.\n–\nfirewalls_tab_policies_add_rules\n–\nClick “Add”\n–\nfirewalls_tab_policies_list\n–\nNow that you have successfully created some rules and a policy, it is time to create the firewall. Go to “Firewalls” tab and click “Create Firewall”\nName : Something that you can remember.\nDescription : Provide a description for your own reference\nPolicy, select a policy created in step 3.\nClick “Add”\n–\nfirewalls_tab_firewall_add_firewall\n–\nFirewall Status will change from “PENDING_CREATE” to “ACTIVE” in few seconds. You have successfully created a firewall.\n–\nfirewalls_tab_firwall_list\n–\nCongratulations, now your virtual data-center has a firewall to control security.",
