      {
         "qid": "10",
         "q": [
            "HOW DO I CREATE A PRIVATE NETWORK"
         ],
         "a": "This tutorial will help you setup your first private network for your instances. This is an advanced topic for users interested in learning cloud networking.\n\n* Be sure to not change or delete your existing network.\n\nLog into your Yellow Circle account.\nSelect the Network menu item in the left pane and then select Network as shown below.\n\nNow that you are in the Networks section, it is time to setup your private network.\n\nClick + Create Network in the top right corner\n\nYou can give your network any name you want, but we recommend Private Network for beginners.\nLeave Admin State as is. It should be UP.\nLeave Create Subnet checked, and click next.\n\nAfter clicking Next, it will be time to create the subnet. In Subnet Name, put My Subnet.\nIn network address, enter 192.168.1.0/24\nLeave IP Version on IPv4\nIn gateway IP, put 192.168.1.1 and click next. See screenshot below for reference.\n\nThe next screen is subnet details. See the screen shot below.\nCopy the following text into the Allocation Pools: 192.168.1.100,192.168.1.254\nNote there is not space between 100 and 192.\nCopy and paste the below text into the DNS Name Servers\n8.8.8.8\n8.8.4.4\n\nVerify your subnet details page looks like the picture above and click Create.\nNow your private network is created and you’re ready to begin spinning up instances.\nReturn to Getting Started and continue the series to spinning up your first instance.",
