         "a": "IMPORTANT: This is an advanced tutorial for students interested in learning about cloud-based routers.\n\nLogin to your cloud dashboard with userid / password provided in an email.\n\nIn dashboard, expand “Network” from left navigation menu.\ndashboard_panel_network\n\nSelect “Routers“.\ndashboard_panel_network_router_create\n\nClick “+ Create Router“\nProvide your router a Name (Recommended name is XX-Router-N where XX are tenant initials, and N is an integer).\ndashboard_panel_network_router_create_form\n\nClick on “Set Gateway” to connect “XX-Router-N” to external network so that network traffic can reach servers outside you networks. You must “Set Gateway” if you want your virtual machines to be able to reach internet.\ndashboard_panel_network_router_list\n\nExternal Network – Select “Cloud External Network”\n–\ndashboard_panel_network_router_set_gateway_form\nClick “Set Gateway“\nCongratulations, you have successfully created your first router in the cloud, and connected it to external network.",
