         "qid": "8",
         "q": [
            "HOW DO I SPIN UP A VIRTUAL INSTANCE OR MACHINE"
         ],
         "a": "Log into your Yellow Circle Account\nIn the Computer menu, select Instances as shown below.\n\nYou are now in the Instances overview, which is probably blank if this is your first time.\nIn the top menu, click on Launch Instance. \nGive your instance a name. I recommend Linux mint, then click next.\nIn the filter menu, type mint. Linux-mint-live-cd will then display. Click the + button to the right of it and Click next.      See below for reference.\n\nYou will now be in the Flavor menu. Flavor refers to the size of the instance such as memory, processor, disk space, etc. Find lab.medium and press the + button to the right.\nClick Launch Instance. If it’s grayed out, go to the bottom of this tutorial for help.\nYour instance will then begin to spawn as shown below.\n\nWithin a few moments your instance will be ready. It will stop being orange, and the status will be Active.\n\nConsole into your new instance by clicking the drop down menu on the right and select console.\n\nYou will now see your desktop. You will want to click on the “Click here to show console” link to begin using the instance. You will find it in the blue text box above your instance. Read the whole text box to understand how to use this option.\n\n*If Launch Instance is grayed out, you either missed a step in this tutorial, or you have not completed the Creating a Private Network tutorial. Click here to be taken to the tutorial for assistance.",
