            "MY INSTANCES SEEM TO BE SHUTOFF EVERY WEEK. WHY?"
         ],
         "a": "There are two reasons for this:\n\nYellow Circle is a learning platform, and not an environment for other purposes such as hosting a website. In order to prevent unauthorized use, we shut down all instances every week on Friday. Don’t worry, nothing is deleted. Just log on and start your instances back up and you’re back in business!\nOur resources are limited, so to ensure there is plenty to go around, shutting down instances weekly will keep inactive user’s instances powered off. This frees up resources for our active users, giving you a good experience with minimal lag.",
