         ],
         "a": "Pre-requisites: \n\nYou must have at least the Plus subscription. You will be sent an email with connection information for RDP, SSH and HTTP access to your instances.\nStep 1 – Enable Remote Desktop\n\nBy default, Remote Desktop is disabled on all Windows based operating systems.\n\nLogin to your Windows virtual machine my using the dashboard located at https://mylab.yellowcircle.net\nFrom “Start” menu, right-click on This PC or Computer (Depends on version of windows you are running), then click on Properties.\nIn the left pane, click on Remote settings to bring up System Properties / Remote tab.\nSection labeled Remote Desktop has two or three options, select Allow remote connection to this computer\nClick OK\nStep 2 – Connect to your virtual machine using Remote Desktop from your own computer\n\nFrom your Windows client machine, launch Remote Desktop Connection, this can be located by going to the Start menu and search for remote desktop\n\nFill in the Computer: – This is the name that you received in your port-forwarding email. It is usually rdp.yellowcircle.net:xxxx.\nClick Connect, and then provide your Windows username & password.\nOptional items specific to Remote Desktop (Display, Local Resources, Experience, Advanced)\nDisplay tab, you can specify screen size, color quality\nLocal Resources gives you option to enable local sound, keyboard options, and device mappings for drives and printers.\nExperience tab allows you to adjust windows features based on your connection speed.\nAdvanced tab provides security and gateway related information. This does not apply to machines in Yellow Circle learning platform.\nYou can also save your connection as a RDP file with custom settings, including username & password.",
